Create a function

FeatureData <- function(data) {
  features <- c(
                "Obesity" ,
                "Physical_Inactivity",
                "Access_Excercise",
                "Food_Env",
                "No_Collage_degree",   
                "Poverty",  
                "Diabetes",
                 "FIPS")
        fea <- data[,features]
        fea[, 1:6] = scale(fea[, 1:6])  # scale predictors
                return(fea)
                 }
df<-FeatureData(mf)
train.data <-df[,1:7]

Create h20 dataframe

train<-  as.h2o(train.data)

Define response and predictors

y <- "Diabetes"
x <- setdiff(names(train), y)
x_train<-as.data.frame(train)[,x]
y_train <- as.vector(as.numeric(as.character(train$Diabetes)))
# Hyper-parameter
drf_hyper_params <-list(
              ntrees  = seq(50, 5000, by = 50),
              mtries = c(3:5),
              max_depth=c(10,20,30,40,50),
              sample_rate=c(0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9, 1.0),
              min_rows=c(1,2,5)
              )

#  search criteria
drf_search_criteria <- list(strategy = "RandomDiscrete", 
                        max_models = 200,
                        max_runtime_secs = 900,
                        stopping_tolerance = 0.001,
                        stopping_rounds = 2,
                        seed = 1345767)
# Grid Search
RF_grid <- h2o.grid(
                  algorithm="randomForest",
                  grid_id = "RF_grid_ID",
                  x= x,
                  y = y,
                  training_frame = train,
                  #validation_frame =valid, 
                  stopping_metric = "RMSE",
                  nfolds=10,
                  keep_cross_validation_predictions = TRUE,
                  hyper_params = drf_hyper_params,
                  search_criteria = drf_search_criteria,
                  seed = 42)

Get Grid

RF_get_grid <- h2o.getGrid("RF_grid_ID",sort_by="RMSE",decreasing=FALSE)
datatable(as.data.frame(RF_get_grid@summary_table), 
          rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = 10, scrollX = TRUE, round)) %>%
  formatRound(columns = -1, digits = 4)

Best RF

best_RF <- h2o.getModel(RF_get_grid@model_ids[[1]]) 
capture.output(print(summary(best_RF)),file =  "RF_summary.txt")
h2o.performance(best_RF, train)

RF DALEX explain function

Create custom prediction function for RF

The following code extracts these items for the h2o example:

# 1) create a data frame with just the features
features <- as.data.frame(train) %>% dplyr::select(-Diabetes)

# 2) Create a vector with the actual responses
response <- as.data.frame(train) %>% pull(Diabetes)

# 3) Create custom predict function that returns the predicted values as a vector
pred_fun <- function(object, newdata)  {
  results <- as.vector(h2o.predict(object, as.h2o(newdata)))
  return(results)
  }

RF DALEX explain function

explainer_train <- DALEX::explain(
  model = best_RF,
  data = x_train,
  y = y_train,
  predict_function = pred_fun,
  label = "Random Forest"
  )

RF Variable-importance Measures

vip_RF <- variable_importance(explainer_train, type="difference")
write.csv(vip_RF, "Variable_Importance_Global_RF.csv", row.names=T)
datatable(as.data.frame(vip_RF), 
          rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = 10, scrollX = TRUE, round)) %>%
  formatRound(columns = -1, digits = 4)
windows(width=5, height=5.5)
tiff( file="FIGURE_VIP_Global_RF.tif", 
width=5, height=5.5, units="in", res=600)
p.vip<-plot(vip_RF)
print(p.vip)
dev.off()

RF Partial-dependence Profiles

vip_df<-vip_RF %>%
 dplyr::select(variable, dropout_loss)  %>%
 filter(variable != "_baseline_")  %>%
 filter(variable != "_full_model_") %>%
   group_by(variable) %>%
   summarise(
            mean = mean(dropout_loss)) %>%
 arrange(desc(mean))

var.names=vip_df[1]
var_1st=var.names[1,]$variable
